name: Captain Fall
overview: A goofy, gullible sea captain is hired to helm a high-end cruise ship and becomes the perfect fall guy for an illicit smuggling operation.

episodes.name: An Unconventional Cruise Line
episodes.overview: After graduating at the bottom of his class, Jonathan Fall visits the career placement center in hopes of finding a gig worthy of his seafaring family.

episodes.name: Baptized in Blood
episodes.overview: On Jonathan's first day aboard the Caribbean Queen, Pedro takes him to explore the new port. But an encounter with locals leaves the captain traumatized.

episodes.name: The Human Zoo
episodes.overview: In South Africa, an eccentric tycoon surprises his wife with an unusual gift, courtesy of the Caribbean Queen crew — and an oblivious Jonathan.

episodes.name: Boner Medicine
episodes.overview: When a married couple visits a swingers' club, the wife quickly becomes the life of the party, leading her husband to seek out an illegal aid.

episodes.name: Je Suis Tanner
episodes.overview: Liza convinces Jonathan to offer a free cruise to an underserved group, but her motives are less than charitable. Tanner, however, could use some help.

episodes.name: Face Off
episodes.overview: Plagued by vivid dreams and frequent blackouts, Jonathan worries something is wrong. Then, Agent Steel leads a bust that promises to change his career.

episodes.name: Cultural Exchange
episodes.overview: When two nefarious leaders use the Caribbean Queen as a setting for their business meeting, Jonathan goes overboard welcoming their child soldiers.

episodes.name: Sweet Sixteen
episodes.overview: At a Sweet 16 for the daughter of a Russian oligarch, Liza must distract Jonathan to execute a suitcase handoff... or face Mr. Tyrant's shark tank.

episodes.name: Family Reunion
episodes.overview: On a visit to meet Jonathan's family, Liza is horrified to witness the Falls' treatment of their youngest son — prompting her to have a chat with Tanner.
